All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddPart_ViewController
    FXML Controller class for the add part view, has format and bounds checking functionality also forces user to confirm when they click the cancel button which gives the user the option to save work if the button is clicked by mistake.
    AddProduct_ViewController
    FXML Controller class for the add product view, has bounds and format checking for input and makes user confirm cancel A runtime error I encountered in this controller class was in the changeScreen method.
    GenerateId
    Generates Unique Id, returns current ID, and allows the base ID to be set to a specific number A logic error I came across was trying to display the ID of a newly created part or product without incrementing the current ID of this class, I solved this issue by adding the getCurentID method which does not increment the ID A compatible feature that could be added to this class would be a different ID being created for either a product or a part
    InHouse
    Used to create In House parts with a full and empty constructor and allow for data manipulation via setters and getter methods.
    Inventory
    Used to create and modify the current part and product inventory, contains adding and removing methods and searching methods for both parts and products.
    Main_viewController
    FXML for the main view scene, contains delete functionality and can change scenes for add and modify.
    ModifyPart_ViewController
    FXML Controller class for the modify part view, auto fills the text fields with the selected parts data and performs format and bounds checks A logical error that I encountered while coding this controller class was in the Initialize method.
    ModifyProduct_ViewController
    FXML Controller class for the Modify Product View, loads the products associated parts and fills in all the text fields with the products details A runtime error that was corrected in this controller class was in the changeScreen method.
    Outsourced
    Used to create outsourced parts with a full and empty constructor and allow for data manipulation via setters and getter methods.
    Part
    Abstract class used to create the base part fields and methods allows for data manipulation via setters and getter methods
    Passable
    static methods used to pass a part or a product between scenes, stores a part and a product and has getters and setters A compatible feature I could add to this code is the ability to pass an associated parts list so one product could send it to another
    Product
    Used to create a product with a full and empty constructor and allow for data manipulation via setters and getter methods.
    SoftwareI_Final
    Launches Inventory Management Program and builds a test inventory and sets the main view as the scene
